    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-04-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-04-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="65"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d65">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3691/383.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of Salvador</gloss> to
                        President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador, Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>,<lb/>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-04-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 8, 1907</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Very sincere thanks for considerate complaisance respecting continuation peace
                    negotiations by Chargé Brown. Whatever good result is achieved will be due to
                    the good offices of your Government and you will have the thanks of Central
                    America.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">F. Figueroa.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
